Thinking more on this, I'd prefer to drop this variable. I don't think it's needed because the user can control whether the ToolResult is streamed via their streaming callback function. 

@author:
Combined with your previous message, this means that we can remove this variable and always prepare the `tool_result_message`. Then it is entirely up to the user's `streaming_callback` function whether it will be streamed or not.

@user1:
Yup, that's right!

@user1:
I just realized we are only passing the streaming call back to the ToolInvoker at init time. Which means the ToolResult can't be streamed if the streaming call back is only provided at run time. 

I think we should follow the pattern we use for our chat generator and only pass the streaming callback at run time for the ToolInvoker too. Could you add streaming_callback as an option to the runtime of the ToolInvoker and pass it at runtime in the agent?
